name: politico
text:
Sean Spicer broke from President Trump and disputed today that there were signs of widespread voter fraud.

"I haven't seen any evidence of it. And again, I don't think it helps his case," said the former White House press secretary
https://t.co/c2aNoeNa1J

name: politico
text: Let's talk about the most unprecedented election in history. Our reporters are live with @SHO_TheCircus to break it down. https://t.co/MVTwugMRn1

name: politico
text:
Arizona’s secretary of state today chided protesters who gathered outside of election offices in the state’s largest county, saying the armed demonstrators might be slowing down the vote tally they have been clamoring for

https://t.co/mVZfVe6TBE

name: politico
text:
Despite the occasional technical glitch and extended polling-site hours, there were no reports of major issues or interference.

Though counting is taking longer this year, there's no support for the position that mail-in ballots were part of a mass fraud
https://t.co/24bbVSUYfi

name: politico
text:
Pennsylvania’s vote-counting is creeping along and Donald Trump’s lead over Joe Biden continues to shrink.

It’s now down to about 64,000 votes, or just under 1 percentage point. But there are roughly 326,000 outstanding mail ballots left to be counted
https://t.co/hTUYu6tqhj

name: politico
text:
So far, about 76% of the mail ballots have broken for Biden, while 30 percent have been won by Trump. If that pace continues — and it’s a big if — Biden would take the lead

https://t.co/hTUYu6tqhj

name: politico
text:
So far, about 76% of the mail ballots have broken for Biden, while 23% have been won by Trump. If that pace continues — and it’s a big if — Biden would take the lead
